---

<BaseLayout
  title="Scott Murray â€” Travel Writer | Discover Vietnam"
  description="Meet Scott Murray â€” 20+ years exploring Vietnam, 20+ trips across the country, 40+ countries. The logistics brain behind Discover Vietnam."
  pageType="author"
  schemaData={schemaData}
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="author-hero">
  <video class="author-hero-video" autoplay muted loop playsinline preload="metadata">
    <source src="/videos/pillar/about-scott-hero.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
  </video>
  <div class="author-hero-gradient-overlay"></div>
  <div class="hero-grid"></div>
  <div class="author-hero-inner">
    <Breadcrumb items={breadcrumbs} />
    <div class="hero-eyebrow">Meet the Writer</div>
    <div class="author-avatar-wrap">
      <Image src={scottImg} alt="Scott Murray â€” Travel Writer" class="author-avatar-large" width={120} height={120} format="webp" loading="eager" />
    </div>
    <h1>Scott Murray</h1>
    <p class="hero-role">Travel Writer & Logistics Expert</p>
    <p class="hero-location">San Diego, CA</p>
    <div class="hero-stats">
      <div class="hero-stat"><div class="hero-stat-num">20+</div><div class="hero-stat-label">Years visiting VN</div></div>
      <div class="hero-stat"><div class="hero-stat-num">20+</div><div class="hero-stat-label">Trips & counting</div></div>
      <div class="hero-stat"><div class="hero-stat-num">40+</div><div class="hero-stat-label">Countries traveled</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- BIO -->
<section class="bio-section">
  <div class="bio-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">About Scott</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">The Foreigner Who Keeps Coming Back</h2>
    <div class="bio-content">
      <p>Travel has always been my escape from the rat race &mdash; and honestly, I enjoy the <strong>planning</strong> almost as much as being there. Researching destinations, mapping routes, finding that perfect street food stall. It started with a trip to Southeast Asia in 2003. One of my best friends told me I needed to see Vietnam for myself.</p>
      <p>I'd barely left the country. In 2003, I landed in Hanoi &mdash; the chaos of the Old Quarter, the motorbikes, the pho on every corner &mdash; and Vietnam addiction began.</p>
      <p>Since then I've made 20+ trips across the entire country &mdash; Ha Long Bay, Hoi An, Da Nang, Ho Chi Minh City, the Mekong Delta, Sapa, Phu Quoc, and dozens more. I've watched Vietnam transform while still keeping its soul.</p>
      <p><strong>I'm not a travel blogger. I work in healthcare IT.</strong> But Vietnam keeps pulling me back, and I finally decided to put everything I've learned into something useful &mdash; a site with real local knowledge, honest prices, video content from the places I've actually been, and an AI trip planner that builds itineraries from 20+ years of real experience.</p>
      <p>It's the resource I talked about building years ago. It just took this long to figure out how.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CREDENTIALS -->
